  "prompt": "What is the best book for time management?",
  "response": "There are several highly-rated books on time management. Here are some top recommendations:\n\n1. \"Getting Things Done\" by David Allen\n- Widely considered a classic in productivity\n- Offers a comprehensive system for organizing tasks and managing workflow\n\n2. \"The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People\" by Stephen Covey\n- Provides a holistic approach to personal and professional effectiveness\n- Includes principles for prioritizing and time management\n\n3. \"Deep Work\" by Cal Newport\n- Focuses on creating meaningful, focused work in a distracted world\n- Offers strategies for improving concentration and productivity\n\n4. \"Atomic Habits\" by James Clear\n- Teaches how to build good habits and break bad ones\n- Helps create systems for better time management\n\n5. \"Eat That Frog!\" by Brian Tracy\n- Practical advice on overcoming procrastination\n- Provides techniques for prioritizing tasks\n\n6. \"The ONE Thing\" by Gary Keller and Jay Papasan\n- Emphasizes focusing on the most important task\n- Helps eliminate time-wasting activities\n\nThe \"best\" book depends on your personal learning style and specific needs. I recommend reading reviews and perhaps excerpts to find the one that resonates most with you.",
